fcipMIB.name: fcipMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this module, published as RFC 4404.

fcipMIB.contactinfo: Anil Rijhsinghani Accton Technology Corporation 5 Mount Royal Ave Marlboro, MA 01752 USA. Ravi Natarajan F5 Networks 2460 North First Street, Suite 100 San Jose, CA 95131 USA.
fcipMIB.description: The module defines management information specific to FCIP devices. Copyright(C) The Internet Society (2006). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4404; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

FcipDomainIdInOctetForm.name: FcipDomainIdInOctetForm
FcipDomainIdInOctetForm.description: The Domain ID of a FC entity in octet form to support the concatenation(000000h||Domain_ID) format defined in the FSPF routing protocol.

FcipEntityMode.name: FcipEntityMode
FcipEntityMode.description: The type of port mode provided by an FCIP Entity for an FCIP Link. An FCIP Entity can be an E-Port mode for one of its FCIP Link Endpoints or a B-Port mode for another of its FCIP Link Endpoints.

FcipEntityId.name: FcipEntityId
FcipEntityId.description: The FCIP entity identifier as defined in RFC 3821.
FcipEntityId.reference: RFC 3821, Section 7.1, FCIP Special Frame Format

fcipDynIpConfType.name: fcipDynIpConfType
fcipDynIpConfType.description: The type of discovery protocol used to discover remote FCIP entities. The value of this object is persistent across system restarts.

fcipDeviceWWN.name: fcipDeviceWWN
fcipDeviceWWN.description: The World Wide Name of this FCIP device.

fcipEntitySACKOption.name: fcipEntitySACKOption
fcipEntitySACKOption.reference: The Selective Ack option is defined in RFC 2883.
fcipEntitySACKOption.description: Indication of whether the TCP Selective Acknowledgement Option is enabled at this FCIP device to let the receiver acknowledge multiple lost packets in a single ACK for faster recovery.

fcipEntityInstanceTable.name: fcipEntityInstanceTable
fcipEntityInstanceTable.description: Information about this FCIP device's existing instances of FCIP entities.

fcipEntityInstanceEntry.name: fcipEntityInstanceEntry
fcipEntityInstanceEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP entity table with information about a particular FCIP entity. Once a row has been created, it is non-volatile across agent restarts until it is deleted.

fcipEntityId.name: fcipEntityId
fcipEntityId.reference: RFC 3821, Section 7.1, FCIP Special Frame Format

fcipEntityName.name: fcipEntityName
fcipEntityName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this FCIP entity.

fcipEntityAddressType.name: fcipEntityAddressType
fcipEntityAddressType.description: The type of Internet address by which the entity is reachable. Only address types IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.

fcipEntityAddress.name: fcipEntityAddress
fcipEntityAddress.description: The Internet address for the entity, if configured. The format of this address is determined by the value of the fcipEntityAddressType object.

fcipEntityTcpConnPort.name: fcipEntityTcpConnPort
fcipEntityTcpConnPort.description: A TCP port other than the FCIP Well-Known port on which the FCIP entity listens for new TCP connection requests. It contains the value zero(0) if the FCIP Entity only listens on the Well-Known port.

fcipEntitySeqNumWrap.name: fcipEntitySeqNumWrap
fcipEntitySeqNumWrap.reference: The PAWS option is defined in RFC 1323.
fcipEntitySeqNumWrap.description: An indication of whether the FCIP Entity supports protection against sequence number wrap.

fcipEntityPHBSupport.name: fcipEntityPHBSupport
fcipEntityPHBSupport.reference: Per hop behavior is defined in RFC 2474, definition of the Differentiated Services Field.
fcipEntityPHBSupport.description: An indication of whether the FCIP Entity supports PHB IP quality of service (QoS).

fcipEntityStatus.name: fcipEntityStatus
fcipEntityStatus.description: This object specifies the operational status of the row. When a management station sets the status to active(1), then the values for the objects fcipEntityName, fcipEntityAddressType, and fcipEntityAddress should be supplied as part of the set request. The values of the objects fcipEntityName, fcipEntityAddressType, and fcipEntityAddress can be changed if the row status is in active state. The object fcipEntityTcpConnPort takes the default value zero(0), if no value is supplied at the time of row creation. Setting the status to destroy(6) deletes the specified FCIP entity instance row from the table. It also deletes all the rows corresponding to the specified FCIP entity from the fcipLinkTable and fcipTcpConnTable tables.

fcipLinkTable.name: fcipLinkTable
fcipLinkTable.description: Information about FCIP links that exist on this device.

fcipLinkEntry.name: fcipLinkEntry
fcipLinkEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP link table containing information about a particular FCIP link. The values of the read-create objects in this table are persistent across system restarts.

fcipLinkIndex.name: fcipLinkIndex
fcipLinkIndex.description: An arbitrary integer that uniquely identifies one FCIP link within an FCIP entity.

fcipLinkIfIndex.name: fcipLinkIfIndex
fcipLinkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the virtual interface corresponding to the FCIP Link running over TCP/IP.

fcipLinkCost.name: fcipLinkCost
fcipLinkCost.description: The FSPF cost associated with this FCIP Link.

fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode.name: fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode
fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode.description: The mode of the local end of the FCIP link.

fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddressType.name: fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddressType
fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddressType.description: The type of Internet address contained in the corresponding instance of fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddress. Only address types IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.

fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddress.name: fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddress
fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddress.description: The Internet address for the local end of this FCIP Link. The format of this object is determined by the value of the fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddressType object.

fcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN.name: fcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN
fcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN.reference: RFC 3821, Section 7.1, FCIP Special Frame Format
fcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN.description: The World Wide Name of the remote FC Fabric Entity.

fcipLinkRemFcipEntityId.name: fcipLinkRemFcipEntityId
fcipLinkRemFcipEntityId.reference: RFC 3821, Section 7.1, FCIP Special Frame Format

fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddressType.name: fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddressType
fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddressType.description: The type of Internet address contained in the corresponding instance of fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress. Only address types IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.

fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress.name: fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress
fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress.description: The Internet address for the remote end of this FCIP Link. The format of this object is determined by the value of the fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddressType object.

fcipLinkStatus.name: fcipLinkStatus
fcipLinkStatus.description: This object specifies the operational status of the row. The values of objects fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddressType, fcipLinkLocalFcipEntityAddress, fcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN, fcipLinkRemFcipEntityId, fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddressType, and fcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress can be changed if the row is in active(1) state. The object fcipLinkCost is set to the value zero(0) if no value is supplied at the time of row creation. Setting the status to destroy(6) deletes the specified FCIP link from the table. It also deletes all rows corresponding to the specified FCIP link from the fcipTcpConnTable table.

fcipLinkCreateTime.name: fcipLinkCreateTime
fcipLinkCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was last created.

fcipTcpConnTable.name: fcipTcpConnTable
fcipTcpConnTable.description: Information about existing TCP connections. Each FCIP link within an FCIP entity manages one or more TCP connections. The FCIP entity employs a Data Engine for each TCP connection for handling FC frame encapsulation, de-encapsulation, and transmission of FCIP frames on the connection.

fcipTcpConnEntry.name: fcipTcpConnEntry
fcipTcpConnEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP TCP Connection table containing information about a particular TCP connection.

fcipTcpConnLocalPort.name: fcipTcpConnLocalPort
fcipTcpConnLocalPort.description: The local port number for this TCP connection.

fcipTcpConnRemPort.name: fcipTcpConnRemPort
fcipTcpConnRemPort.description: The remote port number for this TCP connection.

fcipTcpConnRWSize.name: fcipTcpConnRWSize
fcipTcpConnRWSize.description: The default maximum TCP Receiver Window size for this TCP connection.

fcipTcpConnMSS.name: fcipTcpConnMSS
fcipTcpConnMSS.description: The TCP Maximum Segment Size (MSS) for this TCP connection.

fcipDynamicRouteTable.name: fcipDynamicRouteTable
fcipDynamicRouteTable.description: Information about dynamically discovered routing information. The FCIP device may use the SLPv2 protocol in conjunction with other protocols (say, FSPF) for dynamically discovering other FCIP entities and may populate this table with FCIP link information for each Destination Address Identifier.

fcipDynamicRouteEntry.name: fcipDynamicRouteEntry
fcipDynamicRouteEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Dynamic Route Table containing information about a particular FCIP route.

fcipDynamicRouteDID.name: fcipDynamicRouteDID
fcipDynamicRouteDID.description: 8-bit ID of a Fibre Channel Domain that is reachable from this FCIP device.

fcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex.name: fcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex
fcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex.description: The FCIP Link used to reach the domain specified by the corresponding instance of fcipDynamicRouteDID. The link identified by a value of this object is the same FCIP link as identified by the same value of fcipLinkIndex for the same FCIP entity.

fcipStaticRouteTable.name: fcipStaticRouteTable
fcipStaticRouteTable.description: Information about static route entries configured by the Network Admin. In the absence of dynamic discovery of remote FCIP entities, the Network Manager will figure out all remote FCIP devices that are reachable from this device and populate this table with FCIP link information for each Domain ID. At any time, both static and dynamic routing can be active, and an entry in the static route table for a given DID takes precedence over the entry in the dynamic route table for the same Domain ID.

fcipStaticRouteEntry.name: fcipStaticRouteEntry
fcipStaticRouteEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Static Route Table containing information about a particular FCIP route. The values of the read-create objects in this table are persistent across system restarts.

fcipStaticRouteDID.name: fcipStaticRouteDID
fcipStaticRouteDID.description: 8-bit ID of a Fibre Channel Domain that is reachable from this FCIP device.

fcipStaticRouteLinkIndex.name: fcipStaticRouteLinkIndex
fcipStaticRouteLinkIndex.description: The FCIP Link used to reach the domain specified by the corresponding instance of fcipStaticRouteDID. The link identified by a value of this object is the same FCIP link as identified by the same value of fcipLinkIndex for the same FCIP entity.

fcipStaticRouteStatus.name: fcipStaticRouteStatus
fcipStaticRouteStatus.description: This object specifies the operational status of the row. When a management station sets the status to active(1), the values for the object fcipStaticRouteLinkIndex should be supplied as part of the set request. Setting the status to destroy(6) deletes the specified FCIP static route entry from the table.

fcipDiscoveryDomainTable.name: fcipDiscoveryDomainTable
fcipDiscoveryDomainTable.description: Information about FCIP Discovery Domains. Each FCIP Discovery Domain is associated with one or more FCIP entities.

fcipDiscoveryDomainEntry.name: fcipDiscoveryDomainEntry
fcipDiscoveryDomainEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Discovery Domain Table containing information about a particular FCIP Discovery Domain that is associated with one or more FCIP entities. The values of the read-write object fcipDiscoveryDomainName are persistent across system restarts.

fcipDiscoveryDomainIndex.name: fcipDiscoveryDomainIndex
fcipDiscoveryDomainIndex.description: An integer that uniquely identifies an FCIP Discovery Domain associated with this FCIP entity.

fcipDiscoveryDomainName.name: fcipDiscoveryDomainName
fcipDiscoveryDomainName.description: The name of this FCIP Discovery Domain.

fcipLinkErrorsTable.name: fcipLinkErrorsTable
fcipLinkErrorsTable.description: A list of error counters for FCIP Links. Each counter records the number of times a particular error happened that caused a TCP connection to close down.

fcipLinkErrorsEntry.name: fcipLinkErrorsEntry
fcipLinkErrorsEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Link Errors Table containing error counters for an FCIP Link.

fcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs.name: fcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs
fcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs.description: The number of times FC synchronization was lost on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipEncapErrors.name: fcipLinkFcipEncapErrors
fcipLinkFcipEncapErrors.description: The number of FCIP frames received with encapsulation errors such as improper header, format, or length. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipNotReceivedSfResps.name: fcipLinkFcipNotReceivedSfResps
fcipLinkFcipNotReceivedSfResps.description: The number of times an FCIP Special Frame Response was expected but not received on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatches.name: fcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatches
fcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatches.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame Bytes mismatch happened on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonces.name: fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonces
fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonces.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame Invalid Connection Nonce happened on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipReceivedSfDuplicates.name: fcipLinkFcipReceivedSfDuplicates
fcipLinkFcipReceivedSfDuplicates.description: The number of times duplicate FCIP Special Frames were received on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWNs.name: fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWNs
fcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWNs.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frames with invalid destination FC Fabric Entity WWN were received on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOuts.name: fcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOuts
fcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOuts.description: The number of FC Keep Alive Time-outs that occurred on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkFcipSntpExpiredTimeStamps.name: fcipLinkFcipSntpExpiredTimeStamps
fcipLinkFcipSntpExpiredTimeStamps.description: The number of frames discarded due to an expired Simple Network Time Protocol (SNTP) timestamp on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors.name: fcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors
fcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors.description: The number of TCP connections that closed down on this FCIP Link due to too many errors on the connection. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkTcpExcessiveDroppedDatagrams.name: fcipLinkTcpExcessiveDroppedDatagrams
fcipLinkTcpExcessiveDroppedDatagrams.description: The number of TCP connections that closed down on this FCIP Link due to an excessive number of dropped FCIP packets. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatches.name: fcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatches
fcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatches.reference: RFC 3821, Section 9.4.2, TCP Connection Security Associations (SAs)
fcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatches.description: The number of times TCP connections with Security Association parameter mismatches were closed down on this FCIP Link. The last discontinuity of this counter is indicated by fcipLinkCreateTime.

fcipEntityScalarGroup.name: fcipEntityScalarGroup
fcipEntityScalarGroup.description: Collection of scalar objects applicable to all FCIP instances.

fcipEntityInstanceGroup.name: fcipEntityInstanceGroup
fcipEntityInstanceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP instances.

fcipLinkGroup.name: fcipLinkGroup
fcipLinkGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links.

fcipTcpConnGroup.name: fcipTcpConnGroup
fcipTcpConnGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP TCP connections.

fcipDiscoveryDomainGroup.name: fcipDiscoveryDomainGroup
fcipDiscoveryDomainGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Discovery Domains.

fcipLinkErrorsGroup.name: fcipLinkErrorsGroup
fcipLinkErrorsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP link errors.

fcipDynamicRouteGroup.name: fcipDynamicRouteGroup
fcipDynamicRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP dynamic routes.

fcipStaticRouteGroup.name: fcipStaticRouteGroup
fcipStaticRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP static routes.
